metadata.description:
on monday i went to big bear with a bunch of my friends to see the first snowfall of the year, but it ended up just torrentially raining for the first day, like so bad that the power went out.

we finally got our snow, and that day the crypto market imploded, my friend crashed his car, AND i got sick. 

i managed to get out of bed over the next two days enough to appreciate the snow outside, but was pretty fucking bedridden. so much so that i missed uploading friday's song yesterday.

so i wrote this to cheat the system.

lyrics.text:
I went to big bear for the week 

And now my throats too sore to speak 

But I’m still glad I got to see the snow 

Both Pedro and the market crashed 

I almost had a heart attack 

The cops showed up 

And put on quite a show 

Oh this life’s got some range 

But there’s not really even one thing I would change even if I could

They say that when it rains it pours   

My plants aren’t thirsty any more 

It probably wasn’t a good plan to drive

I think it dropped to ten degrees 

These dumb g wagon memories 

Are some of the best moment of my life 

Oh this life’s got some range   

But there’s not really even one thing I would change even if I could 

I’ve got some extra time to kill 

I’m acting like it’s friday still 

My hours are fucked but it’s what I prefer

Three birds are sleeping in my house 

But they’re too cute to kick them out  

Plus I’ve got a few places now 

Oh this life’s pretty strange 

But there’s not really even one thing I would change if I could

metadata.name: it's friday still #1
metadata.title: it's friday still
